## Core Documentation Structure
- User Manual (`user-manual.md`): Complete user guide with workflows, features, and FAQs
- System Architecture (`system-architecture.md`): Technical stack, project structure, and system design
- Business Logic (`business-logic.md`): Core scoring model, STAR framework, and business rules
- Comprehensive System (`comprehensive-system-documentation.md`): Complete system overview and implementation details

## Documentation-First Approach
1. Before any task: Read relevant docs to understand context, business logic, and technical constraints
2. For UI changes: Reference existing pages for consistent styling and brand image
3. For new features: Check business logic docs for scoring models and user workflows
4. For technical decisions: Review system architecture for technical constraints and patterns

## Key Documentation Patterns
- Chinese documentation with English code references
- Structured sections with clear headings and navigation
- Code examples and implementation details in technical docs
- User workflows and step-by-step guides in user manual
- Business rules and scoring models in business logic docs

## Maintenance Guidelines
- Keep docs synchronized with code changes
- Update user workflows when features change
- Maintain consistent formatting and structure
- Reference existing patterns when adding new content
- Use clear, actionable language for user-facing docs 